The paper discusses a framework for Bayesian optimization, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that has applications in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions active learning (cs.AI), Bayesian numerical analysis (cs.NE), and sequential experimental design (cs.SY) as related fields. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
